cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a practical scheme to train a multilingual sequence labeling model using BERT.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the model's performance and accuracy, and proposes a method to reduce its size and improve its speed.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses a pre-trained language model and proposes a method to improve its performance on low-resource languages.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to train the sequence labeling model.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on image or video data, but it is still possible as the paper discusses the effectiveness of the model on codemixed input text.
